      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:50:9",
      "text": [
        " إِلَّا أَنَّهُ قَالَ فِي آخِرِهِ يُفْعَلُ بِهِ ذَلِكَ سَنَةً فَإِنَّهُ سَيَتُوبُ قَبْلَ ذَلِكَ وَ هُوَ صَاغِرٌ قَالَ قُلْتُ فَإِنْ أَمَّ أَرْضَ الشِّرْكِ يَدْخُلُهَا قَالَ يُقْتَلُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Yunus, from Muhammad Bin Suleyman, from Ubeydullah Bin Is’haq, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup>, similar to it, except that he<sup>asws</sup> said at the end of it: ‘That would be done with him for a year. So if he were to repent before that, he would be belittled’. I said, ‘If he were to enters the land of the Ploytheism?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would be killed’."
        ]
      }
    },
